Sentencas: Zr-doped perovskite-type material BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-delta (BCFZ) is prepared and systematically studied via X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis, dilatometry and temperature-programmed desorption (TPD) of oxygen.
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the BCFZ is characterized using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) with symmetric cell configurations.
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: BCFZ not only shows high oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) electro catalytic activity but also exhibits excellent compatibility with ceria-based (Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9, SDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: They have a similar thermal expansion coefficient and no chemical reaction.
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: With a BCFZ cathode, the SDC-based SOFC (Ni-SDC vertical bar SDC vertical bar BCFZ) shows high power densities (879 and 669 mW cm(-2) at 650 and 600 degrees C, respectively).
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Moreover, it shows favorable stability in CO2-containing environment under SOFCs operating conditions.
Titulo: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.2O3-δ: Evaluation as a cathode for ceria-based electrolyte IT-SOFCs
